Global Human Microbiome Sequencing Market Insights
Human Microbiome Sequencing Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 6.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 19.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Human Microbiome Sequencing Market Overview
The global Human Microbiome Sequencing Market is valued at USD 1.5 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 4.1 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 15.8% during the forecast period. The market growth is driven by increasing awareness of the human microbiome's role in health, advancements in sequencing technologies, and the growing adoption of microbiome-based therapeutics. Additionally, the demand for personalized medicine is further fueling the market. Rising investments in microbiome research and innovations in sequencing platforms are expected to contribute to the market's expansion.

